00:45:46.950 --> 00:45:48.284
Send a few guys.

983
00:45:48.285 --> 00:45:50.586
make it so they
can’t walk no more.

984
00:45:53.890 --> 00:45:55.791
What about the bar?

985
00:45:55.792 --> 00:45:57.293
Burn it down.

986
00:45:57.294 --> 00:46:00.530
("Masters of War" by The
Staple Singers playing)

987
00:46:03.400 --> 00:46:05.968
♪ Now. you masters of war ♪

988
00:46:09.106 --> 00:46:11.874
♪ You build all the big guns ♪

989
00:46:14.645 --> 00:46:18.381
♪ You build the big planes ♪

990
00:46:19.516 --> 00:46:22.685
♪ And you build the big bombs ♪

991
00:46:25.188 --> 00:46:28.558
♪ You hide behind walls ♪

992
00:46:30.360 --> 00:46:33.563
♪ And you hide behind desks ♪

993
00:46:35.666 --> 00:46:38.067
♪ I just want you to know ♪

994
00:46:38.068 --> 00:46:41.170
♪ I can never done nothin’... ♪

995
00:46:44.841 --> 00:46:46.376
We gotta go.

996
00:46:46.377 --> 00:46:48.745
("Masters of War" by The
Staple Singers continues)

997
00:46:49.747 --> 00:46:54.116
♪ You play with
my world. mm. mm ♪

998
00:46:55.285 --> 00:46:57.653
♪ Like it’s your little toy ♪

999
00:46:59.456 --> 00:47:00.589
Nah. we don’t.

1000
00:47:00.590 --> 00:47:03.759
♪ You put a gun in my hand ♪

1001
00:47:03.760 --> 00:47:05.695
They’re scared of us.

1002
00:47:05.696 --> 00:47:08.798
♪ And you hide from my eyes ♪

1003
00:47:11.034 --> 00:47:12.935
♪ Then you try to
run farther... ♪

1004
00:47:12.936 --> 00:47:15.271
KATHY: <i>I think
it terrified him.</i>

1005
00:47:18.342 --> 00:47:21.611
You know. that’s a lot of
power for one guy to have.

1006
00:47:21.612 --> 00:47:23.713
You know. to be in
charge of alla that.

1007
00:47:23.714 --> 00:47:25.414
I mean. that can really
mess with your noodle.

1008
00:47:25.415 --> 00:47:28.117
- Cream?
- DANNY: No.

1009
00:47:34.391 --> 00:47:36.359
You know. Benny was bad off.

1010
00:47:39.196 --> 00:47:41.197
Now. I had him in a
motel for three weeks.

1011
00:47:41.198 --> 00:47:42.632
I mean. he couldn’t walk.

1012
00:47:42.633 --> 00:47:44.867
so I got him a place
with no stairs.

1013
00:47:44.868 --> 00:47:47.103
(over TV): This is my
husband. This is...

1014
00:47:47.971 --> 00:47:49.438
- MAN: Darrin.
- (canned laughter)

1015
00:47:49.439 --> 00:47:50.773
(both laughing)

1016
00:47:50.774 --> 00:47:51.907
DARRIN: Oh. we were
just having a drink.

1017
00:47:51.908 --> 00:47:53.609
Would you care for a cocktail?

1018
00:47:53.610 --> 00:47:55.644
- I’d like a very dry martini.
- (knocking at door)

1019
00:47:55.645 --> 00:47:57.647
Italian Vermouth. Spanish gin

1020
00:47:57.648 --> 00:47:59.515
- and a Greek olive?
- (canned laughter)

1021
00:47:59.516 --> 00:48:01.017
DARRIN: Well. I don’t
think we have any of...

1022
00:48:01.018 --> 00:48:02.952
- (knocking at door)
- WOMAN: Don’t bother.

1023
00:48:02.953 --> 00:48:04.520
I’ll fix it myself.

1024
00:48:04.521 --> 00:48:06.222
(canned laughter)

1025
00:48:09.559 --> 00:48:10.559
(shuts off TV)

1026
00:48:14.597 --> 00:48:15.664
Hey. Kathy.

1027
00:48:15.665 --> 00:48:17.667
Come on in.

1028
00:48:18.835 --> 00:48:20.402
Hey. look at you.

1029
00:48:20.403 --> 00:48:21.904
All propped up.

1030
00:48:21.905 --> 00:48:23.172
Like the queen.

1031
00:48:23.173 --> 00:48:24.974
Who you callin’ a queen?

1032
00:48:24.975 --> 00:48:27.877
(chuckles) Ah. you look good.
You’re looking all right.

1033
00:48:27.878 --> 00:48:29.545
The guys thought you
might really be out of it.

1034
00:48:29.546 --> 00:48:31.814
He is out of it. He can’t walk.

1035
00:48:32.482 --> 00:48:33.849
What’d the surgeon say?

1036
00:48:33.850 --> 00:48:36.685
They. uh. cut through a tendon.

1037
00:48:36.686 --> 00:48:37.987
JOHNNY: Oh. Jesus.

1038
00:48:37.988 --> 00:48:39.355
KATHY: We’re outta ice.

1039
00:48:39.356 --> 00:48:40.590
JOHNNY: Oh. yeah.

1040
00:48:40.591 --> 00:48:42.125
They tie it back
together or what?

1041
00:48:42.126 --> 00:48:43.492
- BENNY: Somethin’ like that.
- JOHNNY: Mm-hmm.

1042
00:48:43.493 --> 00:48:45.995
- I’m gonna go get some ice.
- So. uh...

1043
00:48:45.996 --> 00:48:48.031
So. how long they keep
you in the hospital for?

1044
00:48:48.032 --> 00:48:50.533
- BENNY: Three or four days.
- JOHNNY: That’s a long time.

1045
00:49:02.045 --> 00:49:04.180
(sighs)

1046
00:49:04.181 --> 00:49:06.248
JOHNNY: The guys would
love to see you out there.

1047
00:49:06.249 --> 00:49:07.983
It’s gonna be a
big one. you know.

1048
00:49:07.984 --> 00:49:09.384
maybe the biggest one yet.

1049
00:49:09.385 --> 00:49:11.187
Biggest what?

1050
00:49:11.188 --> 00:49:12.654
Picnic. Johnny’s sayin’
they’re goin’ all out

1051
00:49:12.655 --> 00:49:13.722
for the Dayton run.

1052
00:49:13.723 --> 00:49:15.691
Oh.

1053
00:49:15.692 --> 00:49:17.292
BENNY: How long is
that? Three weeks?

1054
00:49:17.293 --> 00:49:19.062
JOHNNY: Yeah.

1055
00:49:19.063 --> 00:49:20.495
BENNY: I mean. I’ll still be
in the cast by then. but...

1056
00:49:20.496 --> 00:49:21.998
Cast?

1057
00:49:21.999 --> 00:49:23.499
Cast. nah. You shift
with your left foot.

1058
00:49:23.500 --> 00:49:24.867
You can always use
your front brake

1059
00:49:24.868 --> 00:49:27.003
if you can’t put
no pressure on it.

1060
00:49:27.871 --> 00:49:29.371
I know the guys. they would...

1061
00:49:29.372 --> 00:49:31.607
(ice rattling loudly)

1062
00:49:37.380 --> 00:49:39.414
You want a drink Johnny?

1063
00:49:39.415 --> 00:49:41.050
I’m good.

1064
00:49:41.051 --> 00:49:43.119
The guys would love
to see ya out there.

1065
00:49:44.154 --> 00:49:45.888
You know. they’re
real worried about ya.

1066
00:49:46.756 --> 00:49:49.525
- I’ll be there.
- All right.

1067
00:49:51.194 --> 00:49:52.327
I’ll get out of here.

1068
00:49:52.328 --> 00:49:54.763
I’ll let you rest.

1069
00:49:54.764 --> 00:49:56.365
Okay.

1070
00:49:56.366 --> 00:49:58.200
Kathy.

1071
00:50:03.239 --> 00:50:04.807
(door closes)

1072
00:50:05.575 --> 00:50:07.343
(motorcycle engine starts)

1073
00:50:10.947 --> 00:50:12.448
I mean. you wouldn’t
really try riding

1074
00:50:12.449 --> 00:50:14.250
- after three weeks. would ya?
- (lighter clicks)

1075
00:50:14.251 --> 00:50:16.418
The doctor said three to four
months with no weight on it.

1076
00:50:16.419 --> 00:50:17.519
I don’t know.

1077
00:50:17.520 --> 00:50:19.621
Turn up the TV. will you?

1078
00:50:19.622 --> 00:50:21.357
(scoffs)

1079
00:50:22.125 --> 00:50:23.759
I don’t want you ridin’.

1080
00:50:25.762 --> 00:50:28.430
Yeah. it scares me. especially
this soon after surgery.

1081
00:50:28.431 --> 00:50:30.266
I-I don’t like it.

1082
00:50:31.968 --> 00:50:34.470
- You don’t like it?
- I get worried.

1083
00:50:41.111 --> 00:50:42.778
I should just go.

1084
00:50:44.247 --> 00:50:45.881
I’m just gonna leave.

1085
00:50:45.882 --> 00:50:47.983
- What?
- No. it’s better.

1086
00:50:47.984 --> 00:50:50.119
- You’d be better off.
- Stop. Stop it.

1087
00:50:50.120 --> 00:50:52.488
Not having to take care of me.

1088
00:50:52.489 --> 00:50:53.955
- Worry about me.
- No.

1089
00:50:53.956 --> 00:50:55.791
No.

1090
00:50:56.793 --> 00:50:59.428
When I heal up. I’ll leave.

1091
00:51:03.666 --> 00:51:05.034
(sighs softly)

1092
00:51:30.860 --> 00:51:32.895
I don’t want you to go.

1093
00:51:43.306 --> 00:51:45.708
(pensive music plays)

1094
00:51:54.318 --> 00:51:57.820
I’m going off the freeway
into this. uh. ice plant.

1095
00:51:57.821 --> 00:51:59.288
I don’t know if you
know what ice plant is.

1096
00:51:59.289 --> 00:52:00.789
If you’re ever in California.

1097
00:52:00.790 --> 00:52:02.157
stop and look if you
want. but. like...

1098
00:52:02.158 --> 00:52:03.392
Hey. Kathy.

1099
00:52:03.393 --> 00:52:05.361
KATHY: Hey.
Brucie. How’s Gail?

1100
00:52:05.362 --> 00:52:07.930
She’s good. She’s. uh. got a
job doin’ nails in Oak Park.

1101
00:52:07.931 --> 00:52:09.198
I’ll go see her.

1102
00:52:09.199 --> 00:52:10.866
Uh. Johnny. can we talk?

1103
00:52:10.867 --> 00:52:12.902
Mm.

1104
00:52:15.239 --> 00:52:17.940
Oh. you always gotta have these
guys around to hear everything?

1105
00:52:17.941 --> 00:52:20.242
- Well. what’s there to hear?
- Some things.

1106
00:52:20.243 --> 00:52:21.377
Oh.

1107
00:52:31.254 --> 00:52:33.088
You need somethin’. Kathy?

1108
00:52:36.192 --> 00:52:37.392
You can’t have him.

1109
00:52:37.393 --> 00:52:38.894
Who?

1110
00:52:38.895 --> 00:52:40.729
You know exactly who
I’m talkin’ about.

1111
00:52:40.730 --> 00:52:42.198
Benny. You can’t have him.

1112
00:52:42.199 --> 00:52:43.900
The club can’t have
him. He’s mine.

1113
00:52:43.901 --> 00:52:45.734
You know. and if he
keeps ridin’ motorcycles.

1114
00:52:45.735 --> 00:52:47.069
he’s gonna die.

1115
00:52:47.070 --> 00:52:48.303
One way or another.
it’ll kill him.

1116
00:52:48.304 --> 00:52:49.705
And you know this is true.

1117
00:52:49.706 --> 00:52:51.574
What am I supposed
to do about it?

1118
00:52:51.575 --> 00:52:55.411
You know I don’t run Benny.
just like you don’t run Benny.

1119
00:52:55.412 --> 00:52:58.380
There ain’t nobody can
tell that kid nothin’.

1120
00:52:58.381 --> 00:53:00.082
He’s grown.

1121
00:53:01.218 --> 00:53:03.786
If he wants to ride a
bike. he’ll ride a bike.

1122
00:53:03.787 --> 00:53:05.287
Well. not if you
tell him. Johnny.

1123
00:53:05.288 --> 00:53:06.722
Not if you tell him
he’s outta the club.

1124
00:53:06.723 --> 00:53:09.491
- Come on.
- No. he’s mine. Johnny. Mine.

1125
00:53:09.492 --> 00:53:10.726
I’m his wife. not you.

1126
00:53:10.727 --> 00:53:12.461
Fuck is that supposed to mean?

1127
00:53:12.462 --> 00:53:14.129
Well. I know you love
him. I love him. too.

1128
00:53:14.130 --> 00:53:16.565
That’s why you gotta do this.

1129
00:53:16.566 --> 00:53:18.133
(sighs)

1130
00:53:18.734 --> 00:53:20.769
Uh...

1131
00:53:23.039 --> 00:53:24.840
Are you. are you done?

1132
00:53:26.242 --> 00:53:27.476
I don’t know. Am I?

1133
00:53:27.477 --> 00:53:28.643
Oh. you got anything
more to say?

1134
00:53:28.644 --> 00:53:29.912
No. I said it.

1135
00:53:29.913 --> 00:53:31.747
All right. then.
you know. y-you are.

1136
00:53:31.748 --> 00:53:33.281
You’re...

1137
00:53:33.282 --> 00:53:34.450
You’re done.

1138
00:53:36.419 --> 00:53:37.886
(sighs)

1139
00:53:46.463 --> 00:53:48.063
KATHY: You can’t have him!

1140
00:53:56.273 --> 00:53:58.841
MAN (muffled):
Shut the fuck up!

1141
00:53:58.842 --> 00:54:00.976
WOMAN: Why don’t you try it?

1142
00:54:03.513 --> 00:54:05.180
MAN: Shut your fuckin’ yap!

1143
00:54:05.181 --> 00:54:07.516
I swear to God. all
you do is bitch.

1144
00:54:07.517 --> 00:54:09.485
Yap. yap. yap!

1145
00:54:09.486 --> 00:54:11.620
I oughta shut that fuckin’
mouth of yours for good.

1146
00:54:11.621 --> 00:54:13.055
WOMAN: If you did.
it’d be the first thing

1147
00:54:13.056 --> 00:54:14.690
- you ever finished...
- Quit the racket!

1148
00:54:14.691 --> 00:54:15.991
I’m sick of that mouth on you.

1149
00:54:15.992 --> 00:54:17.560
WOMAN: worthless
piece of shit!

1150
00:54:17.561 --> 00:54:19.662
Always acting like
you’re so fuckin’ tough!

1151
00:54:19.663 --> 00:54:21.397
If it wasn’t for my
bad back. I’d have beat

1152
00:54:21.398 --> 00:54:23.031
- your ass blue by now!
- Yeah. lemme get my jacket.

1153
00:54:23.032 --> 00:54:24.466
WOMAN: My back! My back!

1154
00:54:24.467 --> 00:54:25.834
- I said to quit the racket.
- MAN: Come here!

1155
00:54:25.835 --> 00:54:27.336
WOMAN: What a worthless
piece of shit...

1156
00:54:27.337 --> 00:54:28.604
Come here! I’m gonna
put this belt on you!

1157
00:54:28.605 --> 00:54:29.771
WOMAN: you turned out to be!

1158
00:54:29.772 --> 00:54:31.140
- No. no. no!
- Take that!

1159
00:54:31.141 --> 00:54:32.441
- I said. quit the racket!
- MAN: Told you!

1160
00:54:32.442 --> 00:54:34.109
- I told you!
- Fuck!

1161
00:54:34.110 --> 00:54:35.344
(man cries out)

1162
00:54:35.345 --> 00:54:37.279
- (groans)
- Told you. huh?

1163
00:54:37.280 --> 00:54:38.981
- I told you. Didn’t I?
- WOMAN: No.

1164
00:54:38.982 --> 00:54:40.849
- Quit it! Quit it!
- WOMAN: No!

1165
00:54:40.850 --> 00:54:42.017
- No!
- (man sobbing)

1166
00:54:42.018 --> 00:54:44.519
Hey. come here. Come here.

1167
00:54:44.520 --> 00:54:46.088
- Come on.
- WOMAN: Stop!

1168
00:54:46.089 --> 00:54:47.556
- Stop it!
- (man choking)

1169
00:54:47.557 --> 00:54:50.592
Stop it! You’re gonna kill him!

1170
00:54:50.593 --> 00:54:53.828
Stop it! Stop it!

1171
00:54:53.829 --> 00:54:54.730
(groaning)

1172
00:54:54.731 --> 00:54:56.365
(panting)

1173
00:54:56.366 --> 00:54:58.334
I want you outta here!

1174
00:54:58.335 --> 00:55:01.603
Don’t you ever come back
here! Don’t you ever!

1175
00:55:02.805 --> 00:55:04.740
(panting)

1176
00:55:09.946 --> 00:55:11.380
WOMAN (softly): I’m sorry.

1177
00:55:11.381 --> 00:55:14.015
I’m sorry. (sobbing)

1178
00:55:14.016 --> 00:55:15.350
I’m sorry.

1179
00:55:15.351 --> 00:55:16.585
Sorry.

1180
00:55:20.790 --> 00:55:22.424
(breathing heavily)

1181
00:55:25.028 --> 00:55:26.862
KID: Who’s comin’?

1182
00:55:26.863 --> 00:55:30.265
(energetic rock music playing)

1183
00:55:38.708 --> 00:55:40.075
(engine starts)

1184
00:55:49.119 --> 00:55:51.353
- (music stops)
- (indistinct chatter)

1185
00:55:52.555 --> 00:55:53.588
What’s the matter?

1186
00:55:53.589 --> 00:55:55.624
(indistinct chatter continues)

1187
00:56:02.865 --> 00:56:04.299
KID: Hey. hey.

1188
00:56:06.535 --> 00:56:08.436
You a Vandal?

1189
00:56:08.437 --> 00:56:09.605
That’s right.

1190
00:56:09.606 --> 00:56:10.940
All right. well.
me and the guys.

1191
00:56:10.941 --> 00:56:13.108
you know. we’re
looking to join up.

1192
00:56:13.109 --> 00:56:14.609
- You wanna join...
- Uh-huh.

1193
00:56:14.610 --> 00:56:16.345
You gotta talk to the man.

1194
00:56:17.146 --> 00:56:18.847
Oh. yeah? Who’s the man?

1195
00:56:19.949 --> 00:56:21.784
Who’s the man?

1196
00:56:26.589 --> 00:56:28.357
That’s the man.

1197
00:56:30.993 --> 00:56:32.361
Come on.

1198
00:56:34.097 --> 00:56:36.765
Hey. look at this guy.

1199
00:56:36.766 --> 00:56:38.300
- BRUCIE: Hey. welcome back.
- JOHNNY: Wow.

1200
00:56:38.301 --> 00:56:40.469
You rode in all the way on that?

1201
00:56:40.470 --> 00:56:41.837
I strapped it to the bike.

1202
00:56:41.838 --> 00:56:43.305
He needs it ’cause
his leg is broke.

1203
00:56:43.306 --> 00:56:44.539
- Hey. Betty.
- BETTY: Hey. Kathy.

1204
00:56:44.540 --> 00:56:46.542
I need a drink.

1205
00:56:46.543 --> 00:56:49.111
So. uh. what’s it like
ridin’ on the old foot?

1206
00:56:49.112 --> 00:56:50.979
(motorcycle approaching)

1207
00:56:55.818 --> 00:56:57.719
(engine revs)

1208
00:57:02.358 --> 00:57:04.059
(engine shuts off)

1209
00:57:06.963 --> 00:57:08.030
Hey. man.

1210
00:57:09.199 --> 00:57:11.233
Somebody told me you’re
the guy I need to talk to.

1211
00:57:13.436 --> 00:57:14.736
Maybe.

1212
00:57:14.737 --> 00:57:17.506
Blew out here from California.

1213
00:57:17.507 --> 00:57:20.642
Heard there was a big picnic.
wanted to check it out.

1214
00:57:20.643 --> 00:57:22.911
Heard you’re the man in charge.

1215
00:57:23.813 --> 00:57:25.580
I’m Sonny.

1216
00:57:25.581 --> 00:57:27.182
I was hoping maybe to...

1217
00:57:28.084 --> 00:57:30.252
little food. little to drink...

1218
00:57:31.187 --> 00:57:33.822
camp out for a night or two.

1219
00:57:33.823 --> 00:57:35.991
Wanted to show a little class.
contribute to the party.

1220
00:57:36.959 --> 00:57:39.327
All right. Help yourself.

1221
00:57:39.328 --> 00:57:40.696
This here’s Brucie.

1222
00:57:40.697 --> 00:57:43.531
This. uh. Benny right
there with the boot.

1223
00:57:43.532 --> 00:57:45.567
And I’m Johnny.

1224
00:57:45.568 --> 00:57:47.168
We’re the Vandals.

1225
00:57:47.169 --> 00:57:48.570
SONNY: Well...

1226
00:57:49.672 --> 00:57:51.707
it’s nice to meet
some proper fuck-ups.

1227
00:57:51.708 --> 00:57:54.109
("I’m Going Home" by
